Are you a sex worker?

22:55.142 --> 22:58.377
(chuckles)
No. I am a restaurateur.

22:58.412 --> 23:01.547
Oh. I own a few places
around the city.

23:01.581 --> 23:03.115
Yeah. I'm kind of a big deal.

23:03.150 --> 23:04.483
Wow.

23:04.518 --> 23:05.885
You want to grab a bite?

23:06.920 --> 23:09.322
Yeah.

23:09.356 --> 23:10.723
Hey!

23:10.757 --> 23:12.858
You're doing great
up there. You're giving it

23:12.893 --> 23:14.694
- the full Fanny.
- Hey, how you feeling?

23:14.728 --> 23:16.729
I don't know. I don't know,
I don't know, I don't know.

23:16.763 --> 23:19.083
I mean, good, good. But do
you guys think that, you know,

23:19.099 --> 23:21.200
Sue getting up in the middle
had any sort of effect

23:21.234 --> 23:23.369
on the critics or the audience
or anything like that?

23:23.403 --> 23:25.037
- No.
- No, no, probably not.

23:25.072 --> 23:27.206
No, right?

23:31.244 --> 23:32.678
Bravo.

23:32.713 --> 23:34.413
- You were terrific in the first act.
- Oh, good, good, good.

23:34.448 --> 23:35.815
- Terrific.
- I made some little changes, but...

23:35.849 --> 23:38.417
- No, no. It was wonderful. I promise you...
- Great.

23:38.452 --> 23:39.919
- It was wonderful.
- Okay.

23:39.953 --> 23:42.655
I'm a little concerned
about that guy in the...

23:42.689 --> 23:45.157
the tracksuit leaving
right at the beginning.

23:45.192 --> 23:47.493
I mean, he stepped
over the critic of the <i> Times.</i>

23:47.527 --> 23:48.527
The guy was spooked.

23:48.562 --> 23:50.029
- Oh, my God.
- No, no, no, no, no.

23:50.063 --> 23:52.932
Not to worry, not to worry.

23:52.966 --> 23:55.601
The important thing now

23:55.636 --> 23:57.970
is what you do in act two.

23:58.005 --> 24:01.274
Critics remember
beginnings and endings.

24:01.308 --> 24:02.575
So now you have to dig deep.

24:02.609 --> 24:04.277
I know you can do it.

24:04.311 --> 24:06.212
All you have to do is share it
with everybody.

24:06.246 --> 24:07.847
I can do it.

24:07.881 --> 24:10.116
Sorry to tell you,
you're gonna have to.

24:10.150 --> 24:11.784
With all the work
that we've done,

24:11.818 --> 24:13.052
all the money that's been

24:13.086 --> 24:14.453
put in,

24:14.488 --> 24:16.255
it's all for that one critic
from the <i> Times.</i>

24:16.290 --> 24:18.791
If he doesn't like it...

24:18.825 --> 24:20.192
we're kaput.

24:20.227 --> 24:24.030
If the review is bad, then
opening night is closing night.

24:24.064 --> 24:26.232
And that...

24:26.266 --> 24:28.267
is showbiz.

24:39.256 --> 24:41.873
I mean, seriously,
if I wanted to see a show

24:41.898 --> 24:43.299
about an ugly duckling
who gets dumped,

24:43.333 --> 24:44.800
I'd just watch an episode
of <i> Girls.</i>

24:44.835 --> 24:46.269
I hear you.

24:46.303 --> 24:48.037
So welcome to Mario's,
Sue Sylvester,

24:48.071 --> 24:50.039
the gem of Little Italy.

24:50.073 --> 24:52.375
I know it's changed from
when I was growing up.

24:52.409 --> 24:54.744
Now it's pretty much one street
surrounded by Chinatown.

24:54.778 --> 24:56.279
But, still, it's pretty special.

24:56.313 --> 24:58.281
Well, I do like the idea
of naming a restaurant

24:58.315 --> 25:00.483
after one's self.
(chuckles)

25:00.517 --> 25:03.286
Hey, Salvatore.
This is Sue Sylvester.

25:03.320 --> 25:04.620
I'm gonna go whip
up something...

25:04.655 --> 25:06.289
<i>Buonasera,</i> Signorina Sylvester.

25:06.323 --> 25:09.625
This is America.
We speak English here.

25:09.660 --> 25:11.761
So,

25:11.795 --> 25:13.562
what can I make for you?

25:13.597 --> 25:16.832
How about some gnocchi
alla napolitano?

25:16.867 --> 25:19.201
Or, uh, linguine al pesto?

25:19.236 --> 25:21.470
I'm not sure.

25:21.505 --> 25:24.373
And, to tell you the truth, no
one's ever cooked for me before.

25:24.408 --> 25:26.309
What? You got to be kidding.

25:26.343 --> 25:29.011
No. It's true. My parents
were famous Nazi hunters,

25:29.046 --> 25:30.479
so they weren't around a lot.

25:30.514 --> 25:33.382
Also, I've been threatened
with poisonings several times,

25:33.417 --> 25:35.251
so I don't even order takeout
without my food taster,

25:35.285 --> 25:36.686
and Becky's back in Ohio.

25:36.720 --> 25:40.289
(sizzling)
All right, I got to ask.

25:40.324 --> 25:42.692
Married?

25:43.727 --> 25:45.361
I'm divorced, actually.

25:45.395 --> 25:47.163
Um, I was briefly married
to myself,

25:47.197 --> 25:48.631
uh, but it didn't work out.

25:48.665 --> 25:51.834
We both realized in the
end that we'd grown apart.

25:51.868 --> 25:53.703
Huh.

25:55.205 --> 25:57.006
You?

25:58.041 --> 26:00.810
No, I'm, uh, married to my city.

26:00.844 --> 26:03.012
This town is my mistress.

26:03.046 --> 26:04.981
She's my type of gal.

26:06.016 --> 26:07.650
Cruel, delicious

26:07.684 --> 26:09.852
and 100 stories tall.

26:14.024 --> 26:15.992
- There you go.
- Oh.

26:16.026 --> 26:18.661
- <i>Buon appetito.</i>
- Mmm.

26:18.695 --> 26:20.062
(inhales deeply)

26:20.097 --> 26:21.197
(sighs)

26:21.231 --> 26:22.865
I have to say,

26:22.899 --> 26:25.067
when I decided
to come to New York,

26:25.102 --> 26:28.004
I did not think this
was going to happen.

26:28.038 --> 26:29.338
(both chuckle)

26:29.373 --> 26:30.940
(speaks Italian) Oh.

26:30.974 --> 26:33.943
Oh. I knew that <i> Funny Girl</i>
would be a disaster.

26:33.977 --> 26:36.812
I've seen Rachel Berry butcher
literally dozens of show tunes

26:36.847 --> 26:39.348
with many an ugly cry, but...

26:39.383 --> 26:44.086
I did not predict that I would
meet somebody like you.

26:44.121 --> 26:45.354
Me, neither.

26:45.389 --> 26:47.957
Although there aren't
a lot of women like you.

26:49.226 --> 26:52.194
You know, that show
would've been a lot better

26:52.229 --> 26:54.149
if you'd been up there
on that stage.

26:54.998 --> 26:56.799
(glasses clink)

